            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EDavid%20recounts%20how%20God%20gave%20him%20overwhelming%20victory%20over%20any%20and%20every%20enemy%20that%20attacked%20him.%20He%20did%20not%20enter%20into%20agreements%20with%20his%20attackers-he%20defeated%20them!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EYou%20must%20begin%20to%20see%20your%20spiritual%20enemies%20as%20they%20truly%20are-%20already%20defeated%20in%20Christ%20and%20subject%20to%20your%20spiritual%20authority.%20Make%20no%20compromises%20and%20take%20no%20prisoners!%20Be%20ruthless%20against%20every%20high%20thought%20that%20exalts%20itself%20above%20the%20knowledge%20of%20God%20(2%20Corinthians%2010%3A5)%2C%20never%20wavering%20in%20your%20spiritual%20warfare%20against%20God's%20enemies.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPaul%20states%20that%20in%20all%20these%20things%20you%20are%20more%20than%20a%20conqueror%20through%20Him%20who%20loved%20you%20(Romans%208%3A37).%20Declare%20with%20him%2C%20%22And%20I%20am%20convinced%20that%20nothing%20can%20ever%20separate%20us%20from%20his%20love.%20Death%20can't%2C%20and%20life%20can't.%20The%20angels%20can't%2C%20and%20the%20demons%20can't.%20Our%20fears%20for%20today%2C%20our%20worries%20about%20tomorrow%2C%20and%20even%20the%20powers%20of%20hell%20can't%20keep%20God's%20love%20away.%20Whether%20we%20are%20high%20above%20the%20sky%20or%20in%20the%20deepest%20ocean%2C%20nothing%20in%20all%20creation%20will%20ever%20be%20able%20to%20separate%20us%20from%20the%20love%20of%20God%20that%20is%20revealed%20in%20Christ%20Jesus%20our%20Lord%22%20(vv.%2038-39).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGo%20forward%20against%20your%20enemies%2C%20and%20don't%20stop%20until%20they%20have%20been%20crushed%20under%20your%20feet!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
