            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Chr.11:1-13:22",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Chronicles%2011%3A1-13%3A22%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EShemaiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Prophecy%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Rehoboam%20arrived%20at%20Jerusalem%2C%20he%20mobilized%20the%20men%20of%20Judah%20and%20Benjamin%26%23x2014%3B180%2C000%20select%20troops%26%23x2014%3Bto%20fight%20against%20Israel%20and%20to%20restore%20the%20kingdom%20to%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%20to%20Shemaiah%2C%20the%20man%20of%20God%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BSay%20to%20Rehoboam%20son%20of%20Solomon%2C%20king%20of%20Judah%2C%20and%20to%20all%20the%20Israelites%20in%20Judah%20and%20Benjamin%3A%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2018%3BThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%3A%20Do%20not%20fight%20against%20your%20relatives.%20Go%20back%20home%2C%20for%20what%20has%20happened%20is%20my%20doing!%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%20So%20they%20obeyed%20the%20message%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20did%20not%20fight%20against%20Jeroboam.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ERehoboam%20Fortifies%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3ERehoboam%20remained%20in%20Jerusalem%20and%20fortified%20various%20towns%20for%20the%20defense%20of%20Judah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20built%20up%20Bethlehem%2C%20Etam%2C%20Tekoa%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EBeth-zur%2C%20Soco%2C%20Adullam%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EGath%2C%20Mareshah%2C%20Ziph%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EAdoraim%2C%20Lachish%2C%20Azekah%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EZorah%2C%20Aijalon%2C%20and%20Hebron.%20These%20became%20the%20fortified%20towns%20of%20Judah%20and%20Benjamin.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3ERehoboam%20strengthened%20their%20defenses%20and%20stationed%20commanders%20in%20them%2C%20and%20he%20stored%20supplies%20of%20food%2C%20olive%20oil%2C%20and%20wine.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20also%20put%20shields%20and%20spears%20in%20these%20towns%20as%20a%20further%20safety%20measure.%20So%20only%20Judah%20and%20Benjamin%20remained%20under%20his%20control.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20all%20the%20priests%20and%20Levites%20living%20among%20the%20northern%20tribes%20of%20Israel%20sided%20with%20Rehoboam.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Levites%20even%20abandoned%20their%20pasturelands%20and%20property%20and%20moved%20to%20Judah%20and%20Jerusalem%2C%20because%20Jeroboam%20and%20his%20sons%20would%20not%20allow%20them%20to%20serve%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20as%20priests.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EJeroboam%20appointed%20his%20own%20priests%20to%20serve%20at%20the%20pagan%20shrines%2C%20where%20they%20worshiped%20the%20goat%20and%20calf%20idols%20he%20had%20made.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_16%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20all%20the%20tribes%20of%20Israel%2C%20those%20who%20sincerely%20wanted%20to%20worship%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%2C%20followed%20the%20Levites%20to%20Jerusalem%2C%20where%20they%20could%20offer%20sacrifices%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20their%20ancestors.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_17%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20strengthened%20the%20kingdom%20of%20Judah%2C%20and%20for%20three%20years%20they%20supported%20Rehoboam%20son%20of%20Solomon%2C%20for%20during%20those%20years%20they%20faithfully%20followed%20in%20the%20footsteps%20of%20David%20and%20Solomon.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_18%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ERehoboam%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Family%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3ERehoboam%20married%20his%20cousin%20Mahalath%2C%20the%20daughter%20of%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20son%20Jerimoth%20and%20of%20Abihail%2C%20the%20daughter%20of%20Eliab%20son%20of%20Jesse.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_19%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EMahalath%20had%20three%20sons%26%23x2014%3BJeush%2C%20Shemariah%2C%20and%20Zaham.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_20%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3ELater%20Rehoboam%20married%20another%20cousin%2C%20Maacah%2C%20the%20granddaughter%20of%20Absalom.%20Maacah%20gave%20birth%20to%20Abijah%2C%20Attai%2C%20Ziza%2C%20and%20Shelomith.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_21%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3ERehoboam%20loved%20Maacah%20more%20than%20any%20of%20his%20other%20wives%20and%20concubines.%20In%20all%2C%20he%20had%20eighteen%20wives%20and%20sixty%20concubines%2C%20and%20they%20gave%20birth%20to%20twenty-eight%20sons%20and%20sixty%20daughters.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_22%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3ERehoboam%20appointed%20Maacah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20son%20Abijah%20as%20leader%20among%20the%20princes%2C%20making%20it%20clear%20that%20he%20would%20be%20the%20next%20king.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_11_23%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3ERehoboam%20also%20wisely%20gave%20responsibilities%20to%20his%20other%20sons%20and%20stationed%20some%20of%20them%20in%20the%20fortified%20towns%20throughout%20the%20land%20of%20Judah%20and%20Benjamin.%20He%20provided%20them%20with%20generous%20provisions%2C%20and%20he%20found%20many%20wives%20for%20them.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EEgypt%20Invades%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20when%20Rehoboam%20was%20firmly%20established%20and%20strong%2C%20he%20abandoned%20the%20Law%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20and%20all%20Israel%20followed%20him%20in%20this%20sin.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EBecause%20they%20were%20unfaithful%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20King%20Shishak%20of%20Egypt%20came%20up%20and%20attacked%20Jerusalem%20in%20the%20fifth%20year%20of%20King%20Rehoboam%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20came%20with%201%2C200%20chariots%2C%2060%2C000%20horses%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E12%3A3a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Echarioteers%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3Ehorsemen.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20a%20countless%20army%20of%20foot%20soldiers%2C%20including%20Libyans%2C%20Sukkites%2C%20and%20Ethiopians.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E12%3A3b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eand%20Cushites.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EShishak%20conquered%20Judah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20fortified%20towns%20and%20then%20advanced%20to%20attack%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20prophet%20Shemaiah%20then%20met%20with%20Rehoboam%20and%20Judah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20leaders%2C%20who%20had%20all%20fled%20to%20Jerusalem%20because%20of%20Shishak.%20Shemaiah%20told%20them%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%3A%20You%20have%20abandoned%20me%2C%20so%20I%20am%20abandoning%20you%20to%20Shishak.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20leaders%20of%20Israel%20and%20the%20king%20humbled%20themselves%20and%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20right%20in%20doing%20this%20to%20us!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20saw%20their%20change%20of%20heart%2C%20he%20gave%20this%20message%20to%20Shemaiah%3A%20%26%23x201C%3BSince%20the%20people%20have%20humbled%20themselves%2C%20I%20will%20not%20completely%20destroy%20them%20and%20will%20soon%20give%20them%20some%20relief.%20I%20will%20not%20use%20Shishak%20to%20pour%20out%20my%20anger%20on%20Jerusalem.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20they%20will%20become%20his%20subjects%2C%20so%20they%20will%20know%20the%20difference%20between%20serving%20me%20and%20serving%20earthly%20rulers.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20King%20Shishak%20of%20Egypt%20came%20up%20and%20attacked%20Jerusalem.%20He%20ransacked%20the%20treasuries%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%20and%20the%20royal%20palace%3B%20he%20stole%20everything%2C%20including%20all%20the%20gold%20shields%20Solomon%20had%20made.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EKing%20Rehoboam%20later%20replaced%20them%20with%20bronze%20shields%20as%20substitutes%2C%20and%20he%20entrusted%20them%20to%20the%20care%20of%20the%20commanders%20of%20the%20guard%20who%20protected%20the%20entrance%20to%20the%20royal%20palace.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EWhenever%20the%20king%20went%20to%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20guards%20would%20also%20take%20the%20shields%20and%20then%20return%20them%20to%20the%20guardroom.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EBecause%20Rehoboam%20humbled%20himself%2C%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20anger%20was%20turned%20away%2C%20and%20he%20did%20not%20destroy%20him%20completely.%20There%20were%20still%20some%20good%20things%20in%20the%20land%20of%20Judah.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ESummary%20of%20Rehoboam%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Reign%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EKing%20Rehoboam%20firmly%20established%20himself%20in%20Jerusalem%20and%20continued%20to%20rule.%20He%20was%20forty-one%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20seventeen%20years%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%20the%20city%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20chosen%20from%20among%20all%20the%20tribes%20of%20Israel%20as%20the%20place%20to%20honor%20his%20name.%20Rehoboam%26%23x2019%3Bs%20mother%20was%20Naamah%2C%20a%20woman%20from%20Ammon.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20he%20was%20an%20evil%20king%2C%20for%20he%20did%20not%20seek%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20with%20all%20his%20heart.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20events%20of%20Rehoboam%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%2C%20from%20beginning%20to%20end%2C%20are%20recorded%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Record%20of%20Shemaiah%20the%20Prophet%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Record%20of%20Iddo%20the%20Seer%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20which%20are%20part%20of%20the%20genealogical%20record.%20Rehoboam%20and%20Jeroboam%20were%20continually%20at%20war%20with%20each%20other.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_12_16%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Rehoboam%20died%2C%20he%20was%20buried%20in%20the%20City%20of%20David.%20Then%20his%20son%20Abijah%20became%20the%20next%20king.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_13_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EAbijah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20War%20with%20Jeroboam%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EAbijah%20began%20to%20rule%20over%20Judah%20in%20the%20eighteenth%20year%20of%20Jeroboam%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20in%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_13_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20three%20years.%20His%20mother%20was%20Maacah%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E13%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20most%20Greek%20manuscripts%20and%20Syriac%20version%20(see%20also%202%26%23xA0%3BChr%2011%3A20-21%3B%201%26%23xA0%3BKgs%2015%3A2)%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EMicaiah%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Maacah.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20daughter%20of%20Uriel%20from%20Gibeah.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EThen%20war%20broke%20out%20between%20Abijah%20and%20Jeroboam.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_13_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EJudah%2C%20led%20by%20King%20Abijah%2C%20fielded%20400%2C000%20select%20warriors%2C%20while%20Jeroboam%20mustered